The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, September 08, 2003 				 Anxious wait in kids corner
		 Picture of Neglect: The  outdoor department at Vidyasagar Hospital. Picture by  Kishor Roy Choudhury Gopal Chandra Dutta: At Vidyasagar  Hospital, mothers have to wait for hours on end with their  children in the paediatric ward. Senior doctors are absent  for most of the time. Even some attending doctors do not  feel like examining the patients. Can you suggest steps  to improve the situation?																																																													Senior doctors are not supposed to be present in the paediatric ward and attending doctors always try to give their best to patients.
